x = r\cos{φ}
y = r\sin{φ}
r = \sqrt{x^2 + y^2}
φ = \arctan2{(y, x)}
O
L
-L
(x_0,y_0)
 x \rightarrow x-x_0
 y \rightarrow y-y_0
x-axis
\theta
 x' = x \cos(\theta) - y \sin(\theta) 
 y' = x \sin(\theta) + y \sin(\theta) 
 x\rightarrow  (x-x_0) \cos(\theta) - (y-y_0) \sin(\theta) 
 y \rightarrow  (x-x_0) \sin(\theta) + (y-y_0) \sin(\theta) 
